        <description>bundles set [Optional]

Set of bundle tasks.

&lt;bundles-set&gt;
    &lt;!--Zero or more repetition--&gt;
    &lt;item&gt;
        &lt;bundle-id&gt;&lt;/bundle-id&gt;
    &lt;/item&gt;
&lt;/bundles-set&gt;
</description>
        <from>bundles set</from>
        <to>bundles set</to>
      </input>
      <input global="false" required="false">
        <description>filter set [Optional]

The details of the filter as per which you want to retrieve the bundle tasks you want.

&lt;filter-set&gt;
    &lt;!--Zero or more repetition--&gt;
    &lt;item&gt;
        &lt;name&gt;state&lt;/name&gt;
        &lt;value-set&gt;
            &lt;!--Zero or more repetition--&gt;
            &lt;item&gt;
                &lt;value&gt;pending&lt;/value&gt;
            &lt;/item&gt;
        &lt;/value-set&gt;
    &lt;/item&gt;
&lt;/filter-set&gt;

The following are the available filters.

bundle-id (Type: String)
	The ID of the bundle task.

error-code (Type: String)
	If the task failed, the error code returned.

error-message (Type: String)
	If the task failed, the error message returned.

instance-id (Type: String)
	The ID of the instance.

progress 
	The level of task completion, as a percentage (for example, 20%).

s3-bucket (Type: String)
	The Amazon S3 bucket to store the AMI.

s3-prefix (Type: String)
	The beginning of the AMI name.
	
start-time 
	The time the task started (for example, 2013-09-15T17:15:20.000Z).

state (Type: String)
	The state of the task 
	Valid Values: pending | waiting-for-shutdown | bundling | storing | cancelling | complete | failed

update-time 
	The time of the most recent update for the task.</description>
